{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:24:26.676Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Build Timeouts**\n\nI'm currently investigating a timeout issue during the `npm run build` process. Although individual scripts executed flawlessly, the overall build timed out. I'm focusing on the server execution and static generation phases to pinpoint the bottleneck. The discrepancy between individual script success and build failure is perplexing, so I'm digging deeper into how those pieces come together.\n\n\n**Confirming Implementation Checklist**\n\nI've validated that the type files and compilation targets are error-free. Now, I'm focusing on creating a precise implementation checklist for the MVP, which only moves the product to AWS, and connects uploads and downloads. This checklist will cover moving from local SQLite to AWS DynamoDB and S3, including the configuration of environment variables, seeding data, and QA. I will confirm the existence of each required item. This excludes all additional product features.\n\n\n**Defining Access Control Modules**\n\nI'm now detailing the planned access control modules. I am defining routes such as `/auth/logout` and `/api/v1/auth/me`. I am also working on JWT validation, local crypto algorithms, and how to handle tokens in browser local storage. I'm carefully documenting all of the roles, and their relative permissions, in the frontend and backend. Dynamic Clearance Violation Warning route interceptors are being considered.\n\n\n**Constructing API Infrastructure**\n\nI'm now building out the CRUD APIs across both Next.js and FastAPI routes. Next, I'm focusing on crafting a SSR-safe, dependency-free frontend API client. Finally, I'm integrating the interactive AI tools, ensuring they are fully client-side and dynamically saved to maintain the \"Air-Gapped Sandbox\" guarantee.\n\n\n"}}
